The paper deals with image retrieval using deep hashing, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new method using binary generative adversarial networks (BGAN), which involves training a generative model (GAN) and optimizing a loss function, both of which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of binary codes for image retrieval, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on standard datasets, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new loss function to improve the accuracy of image retrieval, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
